# SOLEnterprises.org – AI Coding Agent Instructions

## Project Overview
SOLEnterprises.org is a Firebase-hosted multi-page website with gate authentication, Firebase Auth integration, and Python contact API. The site uses a **component-based architecture** with dynamic header/footer injection and serves a collection of business/service pages with highly stylized, inline CSS animations.

## Architecture & Key Patterns

### Page Structure Convention
All HTML pages follow a strict **"Drop Zone" pattern**:
- Standard boilerplate wrapper with `<div id="site-header">` and `<div id="site-footer">` injection points
- All custom content goes inside `<main class="page" id="page-content">` between `<!-- START CUSTOM PAGE CODE -->` and `<!-- END CUSTOM PAGE CODE -->` comments
- **Inline styles and scripts are expected** within the drop zone for page-specific effects
- Templates available: [pages/_template.html](../pages/_template.html) (structured), [pages/_template-minimal.html](../pages/_template-minimal.html) (blank canvas)
- Example: [pages/Services.html](../pages/Services.html) has 500+ lines of inline CSS for movie theater effects

### Component Loading System
[assets/js/layout.js](../assets/js/layout.js) runs on every page and:
1. Injects [partials/header.html](../partials/header.html) and [partials/footer.html](../partials/footer.html) using `loadPartial()`
2. Wires the "Universe" dropdown navigation with `wireUniverseDropdown()` after injection
3. Scripts inside injected partials **don't execute reliably** – all interactive behavior must be wired in layout.js

**Critical**: The Universe dropdown uses `data-wired="1"` to prevent double-initialization.

### Firebase Integration
- **Auth**: [assets/js/firebase.js](../assets/js/firebase.js) exports `auth`, `db`, `app` using Firebase v12.7.0 ESM imports
- **App.js**: [assets/js/app.js](../assets/js/app.js) manages login/logout state and nav visibility (`setNavAuthed()`)
- **Functions**: [functions/index.js](../functions/index.js) proxies DeepSeek API with CORS headers (Node.js 20, Firebase Functions v2)
- **Deployment**: `firebase deploy` from project root (config: [firebase.json](../firebase.json))

### Gate Authentication Pattern
- [index.html](../index.html) and [standalone-gate/index.html](../standalone-gate/index.html) use hardcoded key `444666`
- Check happens client-side: `if (raw !== CORRECT_KEY)` redirects to `/index.html` on failure
- Successful auth stores session and redirects to `/pages/SOLEHomepage.html`

### Styling Approach
- Global styles in [assets/css/style.css](../assets/css/style.css):
  - Fixed parallax background (`body::before` with cosmic image)
  - `#site-header` at `z-index: 999999` (critical for nav dropdowns)
  - `.site-nav` has `backdrop-filter: blur(8px)` glass effect
- **Per-page styles are inline** – pages like Services.html contain extensive `<style>` blocks with custom animations
- Color schemes vary: cosmic purples/cyans, gold accents (`--vio: #7c3aed`, `--gold: #ffcc55`)

## Project Structure

```
/                         # Firebase hosting root
├── index.html            # Gate page (key: 444666)
├── login.html            # Firebase Auth login
├── profile.html          # User profile (auth-gated)
├── assets/
│   ├── css/style.css     # Global styles (parallax, nav, cards)
│   └── js/
│       ├── firebase.js   # Firebase config + exports
│       ├── app.js        # Auth state management
│       └── layout.js     # Partial injection + dropdown wiring
├── partials/
│   ├── header.html       # Nav + Universe dropdown (265 lines)
│   └── footer.html       # Footer component
├── pages/                # Main page content
│   ├── _template.html    # Structured page template
│   ├── SOLEHomepage.html # Main hub after gate
│   ├── Services.html     # Service listings (movie theater theme)
│   ├── store-hub.html    # Store pages
│   └── [40+ other pages]
├── contact_api/          # Python FastAPI email service
│   ├── app.py            # SMTP contact form handler
│   └── requirements.txt  # fastapi, uvicorn, pydantic
├── functions/            # Firebase Cloud Functions
│   └── index.js          # DeepSeek API proxy
└── [site exports/]       # Deployment bundles (sole-site-export/, etc.)
```

## Development Workflows

### Local Development
```bash
# Serve entire site locally
firebase serve
# Visit http://localhost:5000

# Run contact API (Python)
cd contact_api
uvicorn app:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
# Requires SMTP_HOST, SMTP_USER, SMTP_PASS, MAIL_TO env vars
```

### Deployment
```bash
# Deploy hosting + functions
firebase deploy

# Deploy hosting only
firebase deploy --only hosting

# Deploy functions only
firebase deploy --only functions
```

### Firebase Functions
- Uses Node 20 runtime
- Secrets managed via `defineSecret("DEEPSEEK_API_KEY")`
- CORS pre-configured: allows all origins, POST/OPTIONS methods

### Testing Pages
1. Navigate to `http://localhost:5000` (or deployed URL)
2. Enter gate key `444666`
3. Test navigation via Universe dropdown (must wire after load)

## Common Pitfalls & Solutions

### Problem: Universe Dropdown Not Working
**Cause**: Dropdown wiring happens in layout.js after async partial load
**Fix**: Check `nav.dataset.wired === "1"` to prevent double-wiring, ensure `wireUniverseDropdown()` is called after `loadPartial()` completes

### Problem: Firebase Auth Not Showing Profile Link
**Cause**: `setNavAuthed()` toggles nav elements based on auth state
**Fix**: Verify `onAuthStateChanged` listener in app.js, check `nav-profile` element display style

### Problem: Styles Overlapping or Z-Index Issues
**Cause**: Global parallax background and nav compete for layers
**Fix**: Header is `z-index: 999999`, background is `z-index: -2`, page content is `z-index: 1`

### Problem: Inline Styles Not Working on New Page
**Cause**: Using external CSS file instead of inline `<style>` block
**Fix**: Pages use inline styles by convention (see Services.html for 400+ line example)

## Creating New Pages

1. Copy [pages/_template.html](../pages/_template.html) or [pages/_template-minimal.html](../pages/_template-minimal.html)
2. Update `<title>` and meta tags (lines 7-9)
3. Add content inside `<main class="page">` between `<!-- START CUSTOM PAGE CODE -->` comments
4. Include inline `<style>` blocks for page-specific styling
5. Layout.js will auto-inject header/footer
6. Add link in [partials/header.html](../partials/header.html) under appropriate `.u-group`

## External Dependencies

- **Firebase v12.7.0**: ESM imports from `gstatic.com/firebasejs/12.7.0/`
  - `firebase-app.js`, `firebase-auth.js`, `firebase-firestore.js`
- **Python**: FastAPI contact API (separate service, not deployed with Firebase)
- **Node**: Firebase Functions (v2 SDK, Node 20 runtime)

## Key Files Reference

- **Auth Flow**: [assets/js/firebase.js](../assets/js/firebase.js) → [assets/js/app.js](../assets/js/app.js) → [login.html](../login.html)
- **Navigation**: [partials/header.html](../partials/header.html) + [assets/js/layout.js](../assets/js/layout.js)
- **Styling**: [assets/css/style.css](../assets/css/style.css) (global) + inline per-page
- **API Proxy**: [functions/index.js](../functions/index.js) (DeepSeek chat completions)
- **Contact Form**: [contact_api/app.py](../contact_api/app.py) (SMTP email sender)

## Notes
- Site has 40+ pages in `/pages/` with varying themes (cosmic, neon, corporate)
- Three export folders exist (`sole-site-export/`, `sole-website-export/`, `standalone-gate/`) – likely snapshots or deployment bundles
- Firebase hosting rewrites all routes to `/index.html` (SPA-style, though site is multi-page)
- Gate key `444666` is hardcoded client-side (not secure, for demonstration purposes)
